                    <li>Currency - Boliviano</li>
                    <li>Capital - Most people believe it is La Paz, but the official capital is Sucre. </li>
                    <li>Visas - most countries do not need Visas except USA and South Africa. Both can be purchased upon entry, South Africa is about $50USD and US citizens will pay $135USD. This often changes, so check before you go.</li>
                    <li>Tourist Card - valid for 30-90 days based on where you are from. Make sure you hold on to this card as you will have to produce it upon leaving the country. We had a friend who lost his and they literally made him give them all his Bolivianos and Soles to get into Peru.</li>
